  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large Dutch oven over medium heat.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the sliced ginger and cook for an additional 1-2 minutes, until slightly softened.",
    "Add the smoked paprika, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the chickpeas, apricots, yuzu-kosho, honey, and chicken broth, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer, covered, for 20-25 minutes, or until the flavors have melded together and the liquid has thickened slightly.",
    "Stir in the chopped cilantro, preserved lemon, and smoked sea salt (if using).",
    "Serve the tagine hot, garnished with sliced almonds, chopped parsley, and chopped pistachios.",
    "Refrigerate or freeze for up to 3 days, or reheat to serve.",
    "To make the tagine ahead of time, cook the mixture through to the end of step 5, then refrigerate or freeze. Reheat and finish with steps 6-8 before serving."
  ],
